    "And I could feel myself turning back into that pathetic clown I came here to get away from, yes, from the moment they started that braying noise.\"",
    "In this quote, Ishiguro encapsulates the feeling of being faced with past experiences that one would have liked to bury forever.",
    "Cowley and Fester-Seeger (2023) elaborate on how the greeting by the classmates allows them to call forth the absent.",
